# Goal Description
Transition the Supply Chain Disruption Predictor (SCDP) to use raw data injection, update the backend APIs to expose `geopolitical_risk` and new global metrics, and redesign the `App.jsx` layout to a high-fidelity, Bento-style grid with the React Flow canvas underneath.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Refactoring

#### [MODIFY] `backend/ingest.py`
- Rewrite the `ingest_data` to read `global_supply_chain_risk_2026.csv` using `pandas`.
- **Node Extraction**: Extract unique ports from `Origin_Port` and `Destination_Port`. Compute `base_reliability` (mean of `Carrier_Reliability_Score`) and `geopolitical_risk` (mean of `Geopolitical_Risk_Score` / 10). Fetch the most recent `Weather_Condition` for each port.
- **Edge Extraction**: Group by `Origin_Port` and `Destination_Port`. Get mean `Lead_Time_Days` as `lead_time`, and an aggregated metric for `risk_weight` based on `Disruption_Occurred` or reliability scores.
- Push changes with updated Cypher constraints and nodes (`geopolitical_risk`).

#### [MODIFY] `backend/schemas.py`
- Update `NodeSchema` to include `geopolitical_risk: float`.
- Create a new `GlobalMetrics` Pydantic model (`global_health`, `threat_streams`, `avg_risk_percentage`, etc.).
- Update `NetworkResponse` to include the new `GlobalMetrics`.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/engine.py` & `backend/main.py`
- In `engine.py`, calculate robust Global KPIs. `global_health` can track the inverse average risk, `threat_streams` the number of elements with high risk, etc.
- In `main.py`, the `/api/v1/network` endpoint will fetch the graph and additionally return global KPIs computed by `engine.py`.

---

### Frontend UI Redesign

#### [MODIFY] `frontend/src/App.jsx`
- Replace side-by-side flex layout with a **relative/absolute layout**.
- Put `<ReactFlow>` inside a full-screen `absolute inset-0 -z-10` container so it sits in the background.
- Build a Bento-style UI overlay using modern glassmorphism that sits on top `z-10`.
- Add Pointer Events handling (`pointer-events-none` on overlay containers, `pointer-events-auto` on clickable widgets) so the user can still interact safely with the React Flow canvas behind while clicking HUD elements.
- Present new KPIs dynamically in Dashboard cards.

## User Review Required
- Please review if `risk_weight` of the edges needs any specific aggregation (e.g. mean `Disruption_Occurred` or simply random)? I will use mean `Disruption_Occurred` proportional risk if not specified.
- Confirm if you want to wipe the Neo4j database entirely before inserting the newly merged unique ports.
